Hi,

On Gentoo with a HTC One, when I mount it with plain mtpfs, I get 2 main directories at the mount point (media/HTC): "/media/HTC/Mémoire de stockage interne" and "/media/HTC/Playlists".

/media/HTC/Playlists appear to be empty, which I don't know if it is correct or not.
In "/media/HTC/Mémoire de stockage interne" several directories are empty when it is files in it. As example "Mémoire de stockage interne/DCIM/100Media" where the pictures from the camera are.

I try gMTP and go-mtpfs and get the same result with them: only one main directories "~/HTC/Mémoire de stockage interne", but all the files and subdirectories are here. But it is no Playlists directory anywhere.

It is my firts android phone, so I am a little bit lost. But as mtpfs is able to find a Playlists directory, it look like to me it should be here with go-mtpfs too.

Sometime, I also get an error: Unimplemented opcode INTERRUPT

